ob: “Thank you, kind stranger. I am indebted to you.”

Player_ch: “Don't worry about it. Just please don't yell at me again. It really scared me.”

Bob: “I understand, and I deeply apologise. It wasn't right of me to act like that just because I'm unhappy. Because of you, I learned that instead of hurting people because I'm hurt, I should ask for help.”

Player_ch: “What?! I got my arms back! Look, Bob!”

Player_ch: “Wow! I feel different! Look, Bob!”

Bob: “Don't be surprised. You are growing into who you're meant to be, but your journey doesn't end here. Your next puzzle awaits you through the narrow passage in the trees. Remember to stay kind, and you shall grow. Also, don't hesitate to ask me if you need help.”